⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Terra Branford
node FF6 · FF6 · ⟦Terra Branford:FF6:59d7cb⟧

WHO   — Terra Branford — the half-Esper
WHAT  — The nominal lead of Final Fantasy VI — the half-Esper whose existence is the bridge between magic and humankind, who joins the Returners against the Empire and learns, at the last, what it is to love.
WHERE — FF6 · Final Fantasy VI  Framework inputs: Final Fantasy VI (America's Final Fantasy III, 1994)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because she is the question the whole world is asking — can magic and the human heart share one body; because a weapon can choose to become a mother; because to be born of two worlds is to belong wholly to neither until you choose.
HOW   — By the raw magic in her blood and her Esper transformation, by the courage to feel after a life of being used, and by the love she finally gives the orphans of Mobliz that becomes her reason to live.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I was born of magic and raised as a weapon — but I will decide for myself what I am, and I choose to love.

spoken token : deil-ker-seix   ·   hex : 59d7cb
